Female genitalia. Gonocoxites moderately long, regularly tapered apicad, with very short apical styli with tuft of 3–4 fine setae. Sternite VIII (
Fig. 2D
) with very long and slender apodeme, 4.7–5.6 × as long as length of plate, terminating inside basal half of plate, plate short and small, subtriangular, with clearly visible basal and apical margin, the later armed with very short, fine setae. Spermatheca crescentic, differing between the species.

